## 7-Day Remediation Plan

Day 1 to 2 (Containment):

1. Rotate any real credentials/tokens detected in Lambda, ECS, and CloudFormation outputs.
2. Move sensitive values to Secrets Manager and remove plaintext secrets from env/code/outputs.
3. Restrict or remove broad admin attachments from human IAM users where possible.

Day 3 to 4 (Detection and Recovery):

1. Attach SNS/Incident actions to all CloudWatch alarms currently missing ALARM actions.
2. Enforce CloudWatch log group encryption with KMS and retention policies.
3. Enable missing API authorizers and review API stage hardening controls.

Day 5 to 7 (Hardening):

1. Enable ECR image tag immutability and lifecycle policies across repositories.
2. Enforce read-only root filesystems and secret handling improvements in ECS task definitions.
3. Close S3 baseline controls that recur across buckets (logging, lock/MFA-delete where applicable, replication policy decisions).

